Subject: Add maven.compiler.release property for xmvn javadoc compatibility

POM defines <release> only in maven-compiler-plugin config, not as a
Maven property. xmvn-mojo's JavadocMojo reads ${maven.compiler.release}
(null) and falls back to ${maven.compiler.source} = 1.8, passing
"--release 1.8" to javadoc, which JDK 21+ rejects.

Adding <maven.compiler.release> as a POM property so xmvn-mojo can
read it directly.

--- a/pom.xml
+++ b/pom.xml
@@ -103,6 +103,7 @@
         <maven.compiler.target>${javac.target}</maven.compiler.target>
         <ant.build.javac.target>${javac.target}</ant.build.javac.target>
 
+        <maven.compiler.release>${java.sdk.version}</maven.compiler.release>
         <min.required.maven.version>3.5.0</min.required.maven.version>
         <groovy.version>3.0.11</groovy.version>
         <bouncycastle.version>1.76</bouncycastle.version>
